    {
      "dimension": "error_consistency",
      "identifier": "system_handler_ignores_reboot_restart_errors",
      "summary": "Handler actions claim success while ignoring OS command failures for restart/shutdown flows",
      "related_files": [
        "handler/system.go",
        "routines/version.go",
        "system/system.go"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "`handler/system.go` starts `systemctl restart groundseg`, `shutdown -h now`, and `reboot` via `cmd.Run()` without checking errors before returning success from `SystemHandler`.",
        "This diverges from nearby control paths that consistently return explicit errors (e.g., wifi-connect and swap update failures in the same handler).",
        "`routines/version.go` also calls `cmd.Run()` for `systemctl restart groundseg` and only logs; it does not propagate failures to callers that may need deterministic outcomes."
      ],
      "suggestion": "Introduce a dedicated command-execution helper used by handlers/runtime flows that returns wrapped errors, and thread that error back to websocket/API responses (or escalate transitions) instead of unconditionally returning nil; treat restart/shutdown as failure paths when command execution fails.",
      "confidence": "high",
      "impact_scope": "subsystem",
      "fix_scope": "multi_file_refactor",
      "root_cause_cluster": "shell_command_errors_ignored"
    },
    {
      "dimension": "error_consistency",
      "identifier": "docker_running_status_client_init_ignored",
      "summary": "`GetContainerRunningStatus` ignores docker client creation failure and can dereference a nil client",
      "related_files": [
        "docker/docker.go"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "`docker/docker.go:GetContainerRunningStatus` has `if err != nil {}` with an empty block after `dockerclient.New()`, then defers `cli.Close()` and calls `cli.ContainerList(...)` unconditionally.",
        "The same module otherwise wraps `dockerclient.New()` failures for other container helpers, so this is an inconsistent, bug-prone boundary-handling outlier."
      ],
      "suggestion": "Return the constructor error from `dockerclient.New()` (ideally wrapped with context), avoid deferring on nil, and keep error behavior aligned with other docker API functions so callers can distinguish init failures from status misses.",
      "confidence": "high",
      "impact_scope": "module",
      "fix_scope": "single_edit",
      "root_cause_cluster": "shell_command_errors_ignored"
    },
    {
      "dimension": "error_consistency",
      "identifier": "wifi_state_probe_errors_misused_as_state",
      "summary": "Probe errors are converted into a default toggle direction, producing wrong radio state actions",
      "related_files": [
        "system/wifi.go",
        "handler/system.go"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "`system/wifi.go` `ifCheckForWiFi()` returns `false` on command failure after logging, with no error signal.",
        "`system/wifi.go` `ToggleDevice` uses that boolean to choose between `nmcli radio wifi on/off`, so a probe failure silently drives an opposite toggle.",
        "`handler/system.go` calls this through `wifi-toggle` without surfacing probe failures as actionable handler errors."
      ],
      "suggestion": "Change `ifCheckForWiFi`/`ToggleDevice` to return an error on probe failures (e.g., `ifCheckForWiFi() (bool, error)`), and update handler/system test seams so callers fail fast with explicit error context instead of taking an inferred branch.",
